        </li>
      </ul>

      <!-- WKD Delegation Explained -->
      <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl border border-green/20 bg-green/5 p-5">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-text">Web Key Directory (WKD) Discovery</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">
          leter.net implements standard OpenPGP public key discovery via delegation to the global
          <a class="text-green underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-green/80 transition-colors" href="https://keys.openpgp.org" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">keys.openpgp.org</a> directory.
          This is achieved via a <code class="rounded border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-green">CNAME</code> record pointing <code class="rounded border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-green">openpgpkey.leter.net</code> to <code class="rounded border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-green">wkd.keys.openpgp.org</code>.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-muted">
          Delegating to the open standard public directory ensures external senders using PGP-ready
          clients (such as Thunderbird or Proton) can automatically fetch public keys for
          <code class="rounded border border-white/10 bg-white/5 px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-xs text-green">@leter.net</code> aliases.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-5 rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-5">
        <p class="text-sm text-muted">
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Forensic Reporting:</span>
